🧠 Deep Concepts
✔ 1. Streaming vs Bulk Loading
Approach	Use Case
Full load	small files
Streaming	large files

💬 GS Answer:

“For large datasets, I would stream the file or process it in chunks to avoid memory overhead. This ensures scalability and prevents system crashes.”

✔ 2. Idempotency (VERY IMPORTANT)

👉 What if file is processed twice?

Solution:

unique transaction ID
deduplication

💬 GS Answer:

“I would ensure idempotency by using unique identifiers and deduplication logic so repeated processing does not create duplicate entries.”

✔ 3. Backpressure Handling

👉 What if input rate > processing speed?

Solution:

buffering
queue (Kafka)
🎯 SCENARIO QUESTIONS (CSV INGESTION)
❓ Q1: File is 10GB — system crashes

💬 Strong Answer:

“I would switch to streaming or chunk-based processing instead of loading the entire file into memory. Additionally, I would monitor memory usage and process data in smaller batches.”

❓ Q2: Duplicate records in file

💬 Strong Answer:

“I would use a unique identifier for each record and maintain a deduplication mechanism, either using a hash set or database constraints, to ensure idempotent processing.”

❓ Q3: File contains corrupted rows

💬 Strong Answer:

“I would handle parsing errors using try/except, log the invalid rows with context, and continue processing the remaining valid records. Optionally, I would store failed records in a dead-letter queue.”

🧠 2) TWO POINTER — ADVANCED THINKING
🔥 Core Insight

Two pointer is not just algorithm—it is:

Efficient data traversal strategy
🧠 Deep Concepts
✔ When to use
sorted data
pair relationships
merging streams
✔ Trade-off
requires ordering
not always applicable
🎯 SCENARIO QUESTIONS (TWO POINTER)
❓ Q1: Data is NOT sorted

💬 Strong Answer:

“Two-pointer technique requires sorted data. If the input is not sorted, I would first sort it, which adds O(n log n) complexity, or use a hash-based approach if order is not required.”

❓ Q2: Large dataset (millions of records)

💬 Strong Answer:

“I would prefer two-pointer over nested loops because it reduces complexity from O(n²) to O(n), which is critical for large-scale systems.”

❓ Q3: Real-time streaming data

💬 Strong Answer:

“Two-pointer is not directly applicable to streaming data. Instead, I would use sliding window or incremental processing techniques.”

